      <![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 167, Number 20 (Wednesday, February 3, 2021)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href="https://www.gpo.gov">www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. VAN DREW:H.R. 781.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Id. art. I, Sec. 8, cl. 3.Congress is enumerated the power to regulate commerce. Thisbill regulates how a telecommunications company may setcommercial service billing rates for a Veteran's ServiceOrganizations.[Page H325]</pre>]]>
